"title": "1100: God, perfection of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1100",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God is complete, faultless and totally sufficient in every aspect of his being and ways. That perfection is made known in Jesus Christ, and is the ultimate goal of the Christian life.</p>\n<h2>God's moral perfection</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:8\">PSA 25:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:19\">EXO 33:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:25-Ps18:26\">PSA 18:25–18:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:15\">PSA 92:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:7\">ISA 26:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:18\">MRK 10:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:19\">LUK 18:19</a></p>\n<h3>Humanity should emulate God's moral perfection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:48\">MAT 5:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44-Lev11:45\">LEV 11:44–11:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:1\">2CO 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:11\">2CO 13:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's work is perfect</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:4\">DEU 32:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:31\">2SA 22:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:30\">PSA 18:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:1\">PSA 19:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:5\">PSA 40:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:3\">PSA 96:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:14\">PSA 139:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:4-Ps145:6\">PSA 145:4–145:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:19-Jer32:20\">JER 32:19–32:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's will is perfect</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:7-Ps19:11\">PSA 19:7–19:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's words are perfect</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:6\">PSA 12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:30\">PSA 18:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:5\">PRO 30:5</a></p>\n<h2>Humanity cannot always grasp the perfection of God's ways</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:3\">JOB 42:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:11\">ECC 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:25\">EZK 18:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:29\">EZK 18:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:17-Ezek33:20\">EZK 33:17–33:20</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of the perfection of God's attributes</h2>\n<h3>Perfect knowledge</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:16\">JOB 37:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:6\">PSA 139:1–139:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:5\">PSA 147:5</a></p>\n<h3>Perfect faithfulness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:1\">ISA 25:1</a></p>\n<h3>Perfect love</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:1\">1JN 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:8-1John4:12\">1JN 4:8–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:16-1John4:19\">1JN 4:16–4:19</a></p>\n<h2>God's perfection is seen in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19\">COL 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:9\">COL 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:10\">HEB 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:8-Heb5:9\">HEB 5:8–5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:28\">HEB 7:28</a></p>",
